 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>nakros</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Ok:  The way I did it at 51:</P><P>You seem to have no issues with the initial break, so I will leave details of that out:  Except:  Make sure, as soon as the first wanderer dies that you set a timer.  Everything in this room and most of HS is on a 22 minute spawn timer.  I always set my timer for 20 minutes -- Then I know when it runs out, I had better finish keeeeeeeeling quick!</P><P>Breaking the Golems at 51:<BR>You can cast spells at these guys from the opposite side of the square.  If you are pulling north, go to the south side of the square (stand right directly beside/behind the pillars on the southern side).  Pick which golem you want.  Cast darkness on him.  Now, at 51 I think you will end up getting both 90+% of the time.  When you see them both running towards you, feign death.  The darked mob will not return home.  The unsnared mob will soon wander back to the north platform, and as soon as he appears in his spawn position, he has forgotten about you, you can stand up and root/dot in peace.</P><P>If you are having issues with the golems and not being able to single-pull, I would recommend splitting the spawns.  Starting off with a full bar of mana, its fairly easy to keep 4 golems down.  Pull one from north, one from south, one from north, and mana permitting, last one from south.  Then, whichever platform is golemless, run up there and med up for when the wanderers respawn.<BR>This way, after wanderers spawn and you charm/root/dot/whatever and kill them, there will be one golem up on north platform.  Pull and kill him, and the southern one will spawn, after him, second north will respawn, etc...<BR>From my experience so far --> level 57 = always single pull.  I would occasionally get both at 56, but I haven't gotten both yet in level 57.</P><P>Hope this helps!</P><P>nak;</P><P>Nakros Nekrophile<BR>Saryrn Server<BR></font></td>
